quran[78]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,Rahman ne
  55,2,Is Quran ki taleem di hai
  55,3,Usi ne Insan ko paida kiya
  55,4,Aur usey bolna sikhaya
  55,5,Suraj aur chand ek hisaab ke paband hain
  55,6,Aur taarey aur darakht sab sajda-reiz hain
  55,7,Aasman ko usne buland kiya aur mizan qayam kardi
  55,8,Iska taqaza yeh hai ke tum mizaan mein khalal na daalo
  55,9,Insaaf ke saath theek theek tolo (weigh) aur tarazu mein dandi (skimp ) na maaro
  55,10,Zameen ko usne sab makhlooqat (creatures) ke liye banaya
  55,11,"Usmein har tarah ke ba-kasrat laziz phal hain,khajoor ke darakht hain jinke phal ghilafon (sheaths) mein liptey huey hain"
  55,12,Tarah tarah ke galley(corn) hain jinmein bhusa bhi hota hai aur dana (grain) bhi
  55,13,"Pas aey jinn-o-Ins (insan), tum apne Rubb ki kin kin niyamaton ko jhutlaogey"
  55,14,"Insan ko usne thikri (potter) jaise sukhey sadey (rotten) huey gaarey se banaya (clay like [that of] pottery"
  55,15,Aur Jinn ko aag ki lapat se paida kiya
  55,16,"Pas aey Jinn-o-Ins (insan), tum apne Rubb ke kin kin ajaib-e-qudrat ko jhutlaogey"
  55,17,"Dono mashriq aur dono magrib, Sab ka maalik-o-parwardigar wahi hai"
  55,18,"Pas aey jinn-o-Ins, tum apne Rubb ke kin kin qudraton ko jhutlaogey"
  55,19,Do samandaron (seas) ko usne chodh diya ke baham mil jayein
  55,20,Phir bhi unke darmiyan ek purdah hayal(barrier) hai jissey woh tajawuz (transgress) nahin karte
  55,21,"Pas aey jinn-o-Ins (insan), Tum apne Rubb ki qudrat ke kin kin karishmo ko jhutlaogey"
  55,22,In samandaron se Moti aur mongay (coral) nikalte hain
  55,23,"Pas aey jinn-o-Ins (insan), tum apne Rubb ki qudrat ke kin kin kamalaat ko jhutlaogey"
  55,24,Aur yeh jahaaz (ships) usi ke hain jo samandar mein pahadon (mountains) ki tarah unchey uthey huey hain
  55,25,"Pas aye jinn-o-Ins (insan), tum apne Rub ke kin kin ehsanaat ko jhutlaogey"
  55,26,Har cheez jo is zameen par hai fanaa (perish) ho janey wali hai
  55,27,Aur sirf tere Rubb ki jalil-o-kareem zaat hi baaki rehne wali hai
  55,28,"Pas aey jinn-o-Ins (insan), tum apne Rubb ke qudraton ke kin kin kamalaat ko jhutlaogey"
  55,29,"Zameen aur Aasmano mein jo bhi hai sab apni haajatein (needs) usi se maang rahey hain, har aan woh nayi shaan mein hai"
  55,30,"Pas aey jinn-o-Ins (insan), tum apne Rubb ki kin kin siffat-e-hameeda ko jhutlaogey"
  55,31,"Aey zameen ke bojho(loads), ankareeb hum tumse baaz purs (questioning) karne ke liye faarig huey jatey hain"
  55,32,(phir dekh lenge ke) tum apne Rubb ke kin kin ehsanaat ko jhutlate ho
  55,33,"Aey giroh-e-jinn-o-Ins(insan) , gar tum zameen aur aasmano ki sarhadon se nikal kar bhaag sakte ho to bhaag dekho , nahin bhaag sakte iske liye bada zoar chahiye"
  55,34,Apne Rubb ki kin kin qudraton ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,35,(Bhaagne ki koshish karogey to ) Tumpar aag ka shola aur dhoowan (smoke) chodh diya jayega jiska tum muqabla na kar sakogey
  55,36,"Pas aey Jinn-o-Ins (insan),tum apne Rubb ki kin kin qudraton ka inkar karogey"
  55,37,Phir (kya banegi us waqt) jab aasman phatega (split) aur laal chamdey (skin) ki tarah surkh (red) ho jayega
  55,38,Aey Jinn-o-Ins (insan) (us waqt) tum apne Rubb ki kin kin qudraton ko jhutlaogey
  55,39,Us roz kisi Insan aur kisi Jinn se uska gunaah puchne ke zaroorat na hogi
  55,40,Phir (dekh liya jayega ke) tum dono giroh apne Rubb ke kin kin ehsanaat ka inkar karte ho
  55,41,Mujrim wahan apne chehron se pehchan liye jayenge aur unhein peshani ke baal aur paaon pakad pakad kar ghasita jayega
  55,42,Us waqt tum apne Rub ki kin kin qudraton ko jhutlaogey
  55,43,(Us waqt kaha jayega) yeh wahi jahannum hai jisko mujrimeen jhoot karar diya karte thay
  55,44,Usi jahannum aur khaulte (boiling) paani ke darmiyan woh gardish karte rahenge
  55,45,Phir apne Rubb ki kin kin qudraton ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,46,"Aur har us shaks ke liye jo apne Rubb ke huzoor pesh hone ka khauf(darr) rakhta ho, do baagh (gardens) hain"
  55,47,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,48,Hari bhari daaliyon se bharpur
  55,49,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,50,Dono baaghon(gardens) mein do chashmey (springs) rawan
  55,51,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,52,Dono baaghon(gardens) mein har phal ki do qismein
  55,53,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,54,"Jannati log aisey farshon par takiye laga ke baithenge jinke astar dabiz resham ( silk brocade) ke hongey, Aur baagon ki daliyan phalon se jhuki padh rahi hongi"
  55,55,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,56,In niyamaton ke darmiyan sharmili nigahon waliyan hongi jinhein in jannatiyon se pehle kisi insaan ya Jinn ne chuwa na hoga
  55,57,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,58,Aisi khoobsurat jaisey hirey(diamonds) aur Moti
  55,59,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,60,Neki ka badla neki ke siwa aur kya ho sakta hai
  55,61,"Phir aey Jinn-o-Ins (Insan),apne Rubb ke kin kin awsaaf-e-hameeda ka tum inkar karogey"
  55,62,Aur un do baaghon ke alawa do baagh aur hongey
  55,63,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,64,Ghaney sar-sabz o shadaab baagh
  55,65,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,66,Dono baaghon mein do chashmey (springs) fawwaron ki tarah ubaltey (gushing) huey
  55,67,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,68,Un mein ba-kasrat phal aur khajurein aur anaar (pomegranates)
  55,69,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,70,In niyamaton ke darmiyan khoob seerat aur khoobsurat biwiyan
  55,71,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,72,Kheymo (tents) mein theharayi hui hoorein (maidens)
  55,73,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,74,In jannatiyon se pehle kabhi kisi Insaan ya jinn ne unko na chuwa (touch) hoga
  55,75,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,76,Woh jannati sabz-qaleeno (green cushions) aur nafees o nadir farshon (beautiful carpets) par takiye laga ke baithenge
  55,77,Apne Rubb ke kin kin inaamaat ko tum jhutlaogey
  55,78,Badi barkat wala hai tere Rubb-e-Jaleel-o-Kareem (Majesty and Glory) ka naam